Useful Command Line Stuff


1. Deleting all files in a directory that start with some string 'slurm'
	find  . -name 'slurm*' -exec rm {} \;

	find . -type f -name slurm\* -exec rm {} \;   (specifying that it is files that you are looking for)

2. change permission on a file named bash.sh and make it executable for only the owner of the file (u flag). Can also use a+x for permission for all. 
	chmod u+x bash.sh

3. Check the bash version

	echo "Bash version ${BASH_VERSION}..."